WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:01.640
Hey, good morning, family.

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:02.512
I'm excited to be with y'all today.

00:00:02.512 --> 00:00:06.376
I have a word for you.

00:00:06.376 --> 00:00:09.140
I'm trying not to cry through the whole thing.

00:00:10.080 --> 00:00:17.600
The Lord visited me last night.

00:00:17.600 --> 00:00:35.167
Sorry, I'm going to get it together because I've got a message for you.

00:00:35.167 --> 00:00:36.567
Help me, Holy Spirit.

00:00:35.167 --> 00:00:39.800
Okay, all right, get it together here.

00:00:39.800 --> 00:00:49.876
I had a visitation, an open-eyed vision that lasted for about an hour.

00:00:49.876 --> 00:00:59.920
The Lord showed me a lot of what's to come.

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:03.600
God help everyone.

00:01:03.600 --> 00:01:06.050
He told me to do two videos.

00:01:25.267 --> 00:01:26.320
He said, 'I want you to separate it and don't do it all at once,' so I'll give you part one and part two.

00:01:26.320 --> 00:01:41.391
But I'm going to give you the last of it first because it was holy.

00:01:41.391 --> 00:01:58.985
When Jesus appeared, the first part was about the economy and what's coming financially for you people.

00:01:58.985 --> 00:02:08.411
And then the last of it was his heart—a cry for the lost.

00:02:08.411 --> 00:02:12.600
So I'm going to start with the vision.

00:02:12.600 --> 00:02:32.800
In this vision, I saw the sun going down, and the Spirit of the Lord said to me, 'Brandon, the sun is setting on this dispensation of time.

00:02:32.800 --> 00:02:39.840
' He said everything that humanity has been, this part of it is coming to an end.

00:02:39.840 --> 00:02:53.105
The dispensation of grace is coming to an end, and they're going into the tribulation.

00:03:05.600 --> 00:03:07.700
The tribulation is about to begin.

00:03:13.480 --> 00:03:41.236
I saw the sun going down, right where it was getting ready to set, and I could see the sun coming through the clouds.

00:03:44.702 --> 00:03:50.480
It was beautiful, but there was no time; everything was timeless.

00:03:57.760 --> 00:04:01.084
It felt like there was no—you know when you feel your life is moving?

00:04:01.084 --> 00:04:04.400
But it was just a total peace.

00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:09.908
I could see the beautiful colors coming through; everything was so beautiful.

00:04:20.200 --> 00:04:23.350
And then all of a sudden, Jesus stood there.

00:04:20.200 --> 00:04:31.208
He had this beautiful robe on; I've never seen him wear it before in any visitation that I've had.

00:04:34.680 --> 00:04:44.716
It had a white thread that was perfect right here, and it went into another garment underneath it.

00:04:53.940 --> 00:05:07.733
He had a robe on top of it with a hood that had white around the top.

00:05:18.880 --> 00:05:23.110
It was full of different embroideries, colors like I've never seen before, like tapestry.

00:05:41.084 --> 00:05:41.982
He had a huge wooden staff in his right hand, and it went from the ground all the way up above his head.

00:05:46.353 --> 00:05:47.047
It was a very thick-looking staff.

00:05:47.047 --> 00:05:50.520
His face had so much compassion.

00:05:56.480 --> 00:06:00.330
All of a sudden, I heard him say, 'One last call.

00:06:03.622 --> 00:06:06.687
One last call.

00:06:06.687 --> 00:06:13.840
I'm calling my sheep.

00:06:13.840 --> 00:06:14.840
I'm coming.

00:06:13.840 --> 00:06:14.890
One last call.

00:06:13.840 --> 00:06:20.640
' It sounded like a horn blowing throughout this valley.

00:06:20.640 --> 00:06:29.080
I looked upon this valley, and there was a valley of sheep on a green pasture.

00:06:29.080 --> 00:06:34.520
Half of it was green, but half of it was dark.

00:06:34.520 --> 00:06:46.342
All of these sheep that were the closest to him—because he was upon a hill—were watching.

00:06:55.480 --> 00:06:58.980
The sun was setting; it was coming to an end.

00:06:55.480 --> 00:07:11.140
Everything we've ever known as humanity, from the beginning with Adam and Eve to where we are right now, he said the sun is setting on time.

00:07:19.200 --> 00:07:21.300
He yelled it: 'One last call!

00:07:19.200 --> 00:07:31.987
' All of a sudden, down that valley, the sun started to shine upon the sheep.

00:07:45.680 --> 00:07:47.004
There were heavy sheep with big fur, and there were skinny sheep that looked like they had been sheared and were completely bald.

00:07:48.991 --> 00:08:08.680
They were grazing upon this grass, and all of a sudden, they looked to him and started to run to the Father, and he was waiting for them.

00:08:08.680 --> 00:08:21.520
The heavy sheep were running—it was interesting because I could see their legs at a trot, almost like a gallop trying to get to the Father.

00:08:21.520 --> 00:08:30.280
Some of the sheep were waddling because they were heavier than others.

00:08:30.280 --> 00:08:39.898
Some sheep were barely moving, having a hard time, but they were on their way.

00:08:53.080 --> 00:08:56.580
I could see the ones behind; his face looked distressed.

00:08:55.132 --> 00:08:59.920
The Lord could see them, but they weren't watching.

00:08:59.920 --> 00:09:01.344
They had gray fur and black on them.

00:09:10.160 --> 00:09:11.720
The sheep behind were in the darkness, and they were eating, but they never heard him call.

00:09:11.720 --> 00:09:13.944
They weren't paying attention; they just kept eating.

00:09:13.944 --> 00:09:17.920
Time was running out, and they didn't even know it.

00:09:17.920 --> 00:09:24.951
Those sheep were covered in soot, covered in black, grazing upon the land.

00:09:24.951 --> 00:09:43.240
I just kept watching his face as he looked to see if they were going to hear him as he's calling because we're running out of time.

00:09:43.240 --> 00:09:47.036
Humanity as we know it is coming to an end.

00:09:47.036 --> 00:09:58.760
Humanity as it's been for the last 6,000 years, before we go into the millennial reign, we're fixing to go into the tribulation.

00:09:58.760 --> 00:10:12.240
That's what he was trying to tell everybody: that there was one last call, one last harvest, one last push.

00:10:19.200 --> 00:10:25.760
I told you all this before—that the bells will ring in the church one more time to sound the alarm of his coming.

00:10:25.760 --> 00:10:38.440
Now he's given me this; he came to me personally and told me to tell you that there's one last call.

00:10:38.440 --> 00:10:46.600
If you're living on the edge and not living for Jesus, is your boat ready?

00:10:46.600 --> 00:10:51.133
Are you ready for the coming of the Lord?

00:11:08.440 --> 00:11:11.940
Is your heart ready for the coming of your King?

00:11:08.440 --> 00:11:21.864
If you're riding the fence, you better get your heart right before him because you're about to miss the boat.

00:11:24.840 --> 00:11:25.560
The sun is setting, and people are asleep.

00:11:25.560 --> 00:11:31.320
Some were awake and looking for the Lord.

00:11:31.320 --> 00:11:43.560
Those sheep were attentive and heard his voice because the Bible says, 'My sheep will know my voice, and a stranger's voice they'll not follow.

00:11:43.560 --> 00:11:45.560
' One last call.

00:11:45.560 --> 00:11:55.972
I saw that sun setting; it went down, and all of a sudden—this is the end of the vision with the Father.

00:11:55.972 --> 00:11:59.360
I've never seen this before in the spirit realm.

00:11:59.360 --> 00:12:16.045
I could see the sun coming down and the light shined directly into my spiritual eyes.

00:12:16.045 --> 00:12:25.240
I could not see anything else; it was just fire all over me.

00:12:25.240 --> 00:12:26.845
Then the sun set and went away.

00:12:41.056 --> 00:12:41.888
The vision instantaneously stopped, and the Lord started to tell me, 'I want you to tell my people that there's one more call, Brandon.

00:12:51.392 --> 00:12:52.144
There's one more call, and I'm coming.

00:12:52.144 --> 00:13:01.917
I'm giving them one more chance; I'm trying to get a great harvest of souls.

00:13:01.917 --> 00:13:03.568
' He was warning the people that he's coming.

00:13:03.568 --> 00:13:08.267
Pray over Israel and the things that he's showing me.

00:13:08.267 --> 00:13:12.400
A great shaking is coming—more than what anybody realizes.

00:13:12.400 --> 00:13:24.000
People are not prepared for what's about to happen.

00:13:33.240 --> 00:13:33.872
The Lord said, 'Brandon, it's time; you have to get your boat ready even more.

00:13:33.872 --> 00:13:38.296
Separate yourself unto me.

00:13:38.296 --> 00:13:46.600
' He showed me people on YouTube that I have known.

00:14:00.800 --> 00:14:03.200
He said, 'Brandon, they'll be broke within a day; they're going to lose everything because their heart is not with me.

00:14:03.200 --> 00:14:21.040
' He said every single one of them will be humbled; every single one of them will lose it that fast.

00:14:21.040 --> 00:14:22.790
Everything that they've ever had.

00:14:21.040 --> 00:14:38.171
Because, 'My heart is not that any man should perish, but all come to repentance.

00:14:38.171 --> 00:14:48.760
' But sometimes we go through hard times because we're too stiff-necked.

00:14:54.304 --> 00:14:55.488
We are not listening, watching, or waiting.

00:14:55.488 --> 00:15:06.560
We're not keeping our lamps full or making him Lord over our lives.

00:15:06.560 --> 00:15:15.080
He's second, maybe third; you don't consult him at all.

00:15:15.080 --> 00:15:21.810
Sometimes you go to church, sometimes you don't; you don't really care.

00:15:34.097 --> 00:15:35.331
He's not Lord; he's not priority in your life.

00:15:46.720 --> 00:15:52.280
There's going to be a great sifting of the sand, and you're going to see the good stuff rise to the top and the bad stuff go to the bottom.

00:15:52.280 --> 00:16:07.596
There's a line being drawn in the sand, and God is saying, 'Who is for me and who is truly for me?

00:16:07.596 --> 00:16:15.784
Who is truly just riding the fence and who is truly against me?

00:16:15.784 --> 00:16:18.040
' Are you on the Lord's side?

00:16:32.540 --> 00:16:33.232
If he calls one last call, do you hear his voice?

00:16:33.232 --> 00:16:37.855
Are you the one that he's calling that's not listening?

00:16:37.855 --> 00:16:42.800
Is your head down in that grass thinking that you're safe?

00:16:42.800 --> 00:16:55.960
Do you truly believe that if Jesus came back today in the Rapture of the church, you would go with him?

00:16:55.960 --> 00:16:56.468
Or is your relationship with God just convenient?

00:16:56.976 --> 00:17:01.040
I have to ask you these things.

00:17:01.040 --> 00:17:02.440
There's one last call.

00:17:01.040 --> 00:17:06.022
He's trying to tell you that he loves you.

00:17:06.022 --> 00:17:12.000
Do you hear him today?

00:17:21.620 --> 00:17:22.120
Don't turn him away.

00:17:22.120 --> 00:17:26.460
It's time for you to fall more in love with Jesus.

00:17:26.460 --> 00:17:30.880
It's time for you to give your heart and be sold out.

00:17:41.284 --> 00:17:41.909
None of the world and all of him.

00:17:41.909 --> 00:17:43.909
'All to thee, my precious Lord, I surrender all.

00:17:43.909 --> 00:17:49.902
' Have you surrendered all?

00:17:49.902 --> 00:17:51.400
Are you riding the fence?

00:17:51.400 --> 00:17:59.000
Do you have one foot in the world and one foot with Jesus?

00:18:00.813 --> 00:18:04.440
Is it just a convenient relationship because you want fireproof insurance?

00:18:12.640 --> 00:18:15.790
The compassion of Jesus is much more than that.

00:18:29.640 --> 00:18:32.520
If you could truly see the compassion on his face that I saw for humanity—the concern that this dispensation of time is coming to an end—he wants not one man to perish, but all to come to repentance.

00:18:32.520 --> 00:18:33.960
Will you give him a chance today?

00:18:33.960 --> 00:18:39.600
Would you yield yourself over to him today?

00:18:39.600 --> 00:18:42.840
Would you tell him, 'I want you to be my Lord and personal Savior'?

00:18:42.840 --> 00:18:45.211
He's waiting with his arms wide open.

00:18:45.211 --> 00:18:47.582
Stop running.

00:18:47.582 --> 00:19:03.840
There are so many of you running, thinking, 'I'll yield over whenever I get older; I'll give my heart to Jesus whenever it's convenient; right now, I'm enjoying sin.

00:19:03.840 --> 00:19:10.480
' But the Lord told me to tell you time is over.

00:19:10.480 --> 00:19:23.737
Whether that is a year from now or five years, on the scale of eternity, it's nothing; life is a vapor.

00:19:23.737 --> 00:19:27.200
Hell is forever; Heaven is forever.

00:19:27.200 --> 00:19:28.109
Which one do you choose?

00:19:28.109 --> 00:19:37.200
If you die tonight in your sleep, where will you spend eternity?

00:19:37.200 --> 00:19:51.896
You say, 'I said the sinner's prayer when I was a kid, but I live like the world.

00:19:51.896 --> 00:20:02.076
' The very thing you say you were saved from, you went back to.

00:20:03.400 --> 00:20:07.676
You got baptized when you were ten, but you haven't spoken to him since.

00:20:07.676 --> 00:20:09.280
Does he know you?

00:20:09.280 --> 00:20:17.840
People say, 'I know Brandon,' but they don't know me; they just see me on YouTube.

00:20:22.680 --> 00:20:24.080
You don't know me.

00:20:38.880 --> 00:20:44.830
The only people who really know me are my kids, my wife, my mom, and my dad.

00:20:41.949 --> 00:20:47.320
You may have heard Bible stories, but that doesn't mean you know him.

00:20:47.320 --> 00:21:00.880
There's an intimacy with the Father that is a day-to-day process.

00:21:00.880 --> 00:21:13.880
When he said, 'You prophesied in my name, you laid hands on the sick, and they recovered, you cast out devils in my name,' and he said, 'Depart from me, I never knew you.

00:21:13.880 --> 00:21:18.080
' Does he know you?

00:21:19.287 --> 00:21:25.920
To cast out a devil or lay hands on the sick takes faith, but do you know him?

00:21:41.808 --> 00:21:42.392
I'm asking you today to check your heart and cry out to Jesus and make him your Lord and Savior.

00:21:42.392 --> 00:21:46.480
Christianity is not always convenient; there's persecution.

00:21:54.800 --> 00:21:57.950
But I stand with him, and he visits me.

00:21:54.800 --> 00:21:59.840
He said, 'Brandon, the persecution will increase, but the anointing will also increase.

00:22:07.644 --> 00:22:08.215
Do not fear man; fear me.

00:22:08.215 --> 00:22:16.200
' I do it for him because I want him to say, 'Well done, thou good and faithful servant; enter into my rest.

00:22:16.200 --> 00:22:21.400
' Every day I say, 'Father, use me for your glory.

00:22:21.400 --> 00:22:34.000
' For we have this treasure in earthen vessels that the excellency of the power will be known of him and not of me.

00:22:34.000 --> 00:22:47.920
That's all I have for you on this video, but I want to give you all a chance to ask Jesus Christ to be your Lord and Savior.

00:22:47.920 --> 00:22:53.680
Say this prayer after me: 'Father, I'm a sinner.

00:22:53.680 --> 00:22:54.865
I've been away from you.

00:22:54.865 --> 00:23:03.020
I ask you to come into my life and make you my Lord and personal Savior.

00:23:03.020 --> 00:23:05.840
Forgive me and cleanse me from all unrighteousness.

00:23:05.840 --> 00:23:11.640
Write my name in the Lamb's Book of Life.

00:23:21.249 --> 00:23:21.692
I yield myself over to you; have your way in my life.

00:23:21.692 --> 00:23:25.680
You're the captain of my ship.

00:23:25.680 --> 00:23:27.080
I'm lost without you.

00:23:25.680 --> 00:23:32.800
Thank you, Lord, that Jesus died for me and rose again on the third day.

00:23:32.800 --> 00:23:43.222
' Believe it with your heart and say out your mouth that he's your Lord.

00:23:43.222 --> 00:23:54.560
Then go find a Bible-believing church that prays, reads their Bible, and teaches you how to live by faith.

00:23:54.560 --> 00:23:55.610
It's that easy.

00:23:54.560 --> 00:23:58.900
Stop being a knucklehead; stop practicing sin.

00:24:00.760 --> 00:24:05.880
We fall down and skin our knees, but we do not do it habitually on purpose.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
When we mess up, we run to God, not from him.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.450
Our sin is none of the devil's business, though he will tempt you and beat you over the head because he is the accuser of the brethren.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
We have to get to a place where we say, 'Lord, have your way in me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
' That's called grace.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
But there comes a point in time where people make a choice.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
You choose to live in sin, looking at bad things on the internet or choosing fornicating and adultery.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
You can say no; submit yourself to God, resist the devil, and he will flee.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.500
Get yourself in the word, read the Bible, and pray.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
We're all a work in progress, walking our salvation out with fear and trembling.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
He will clean you up; it's a process.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
For those with addictions, don't give up; just keep going to him.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
When you fall, stand back up.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
I bless you in the name of Jesus.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
Thank you for watching.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
If this blessed you, like the video, share it, and comment below; it helps the algorithm.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
Persecution comes for the word's sake, but we just keep standing.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
Put a smile on your face and a song in your heart.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.450
Jesus loves you, and we love you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
We will see you all in just a couple of minutes in the next video.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
Bye-bye.
